channel.title: When was the first Aryan made?
channel.description: So i'm kind of new in this forum as you might have already noticed so i would want to know when the forst aryan was made for rs2 and rsc. And i also would want to know have there really been 377 aryans??

item.title: When was the first Aryan made?
item.dc:creator: @philodespotos philodespotos
item.description:
@philodespotos wrote:

150? Please at least try to come up with something approaching reality.

Aryan was first released publicly to SourceForge on or around November 7. See this link: http://aryan.cvs.sourceforge.net/aryan/aryan/run-bot.sh?view=log

We moved from there to the SVN setup on devland maybe a few weeks later.

Assuming 4 updates per month, that’d put Aryan at around 28-30 releases, but that hasn’t been the case. It’s marginally more than that. But not significantly.

The earliest client jar I have is 332, but how closely that corresponds to the beginning of Aryan is beyond me.

Edit:

Actually, SourceForge tells us the earliest revision, too. Our first update was to #343, so the first public client version available was for 342. http://aryan.cvs.sourceforge.net/aryan/aryan/OUTPUT/Player.java?view=log
